\begin_layout Standard
The gold-coated surfaces of our pendulum and foil are some mixture of amorphous
 and polycrystalline materials.
 The surface environment evolves over time, as crystals slowly change and
 residual gas particles adsorbed onto the surface move about 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "PhysRevA.84.023412,PhysRevLett.109.103001WinelandGasNoise"

\end_inset

.
