 directly, or by computing the force from a large annulus that represents
 the 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

missing
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 mass from an infinite sheet that the cylindrical sheet purports to represent
 and subtracting it from the known-uniform force due to an infinite sheet.
 As all pointwise separations are large in the latter case, any questions
 of grid overlap are rendered moot.
